Had a blast the last few weeks commentating at all hours of the night/morning for @skiandsnowboard.live 😴
I never appreciated how difficult sharing the racer perspective and general commentary would be till my own attempt at it! It is a steep learning curve…😬 I know I mispronounced a bunch of names, avoided saying others, said people would be slow (then they were fast), and flubbed up plenty of other comments but I am SO grateful for the chance at it. Hopeful for more opportunities ahead! 
-
Big thanks to my sidekick @pattypatdown for agreeing to wake up at 2am, bring the energy and humor to so many scenarios! I think we all can agree his future must lie with commentary for the Westminster Dog Show. @wkcdogshow 
Many thanks to @usskiteam coaches @scottyvpeepee for the Bormio insight, (you made it look even icier with your POV) and @iangarner1 for truly showing how a bobsled would have worked better in Garmisch than skis. #commentary #thatbusdrivercanski #bormio #garmisch #skisnowboardlive

All the @usskiteam excitement from this weekend at Cortina and Kitzbühel gets me all fired up! #gousa 🇺🇸 Lots of highlights to reminisce about over my years at @cortinaskiworldcup….double podium with @lindseyvonn and @jacquelinewiles, @juliamancuso retirement run, plus some of my most funnest moments on Downhill skis. ❤️❤️❤️ Way to go team! Keep it rolling ladies and gents. 🫡 #cortina #kitzbühl #skiracing

Another chapter! 📕📗
Thank you to @sscvail and all the athletes, coaches, parents and all those who have contributed to this “second chapter” of ski racing for me.
.
 As turn the page on full time coaching I am so grateful for the last two years spent on the other side of the gates. 🙏🏻 I learned so much, and it was fulfilling to share my passion and knowledge with others. I did some dumb stuff, some smart stuff, and all in all I am glad my transition from being an athlete lead to coaching. Even just for a short time! 
.
I am not sure what is next for me, but after 25 years in the sport of ski racing it feels like a good time to try other things, and see what else it out there. (open to suggestions 😉) Skiing/ski racing will always be part of who I am, and I thank the entire community for that. ❤️
.
Onwards!
